This error occurs when using Tailwind CSS with a framework that uses a different way to manage CSS class names.  For example, in Vue.js, if you use the `v-bind` directive to dynamically apply classes, and you're not careful, you can end up with class names that Tailwind CSS doesn't recognize, leading to unexpected styling or no styling at all.  The error is not a specific compiler error but a runtime styling issue.  For instance, if a class name is slightly misspelled or contains unexpected characters, Tailwind will not apply the corresponding style.